5000|$|<b>The</b> {{rectangular}} <b>Exxon</b> logo, with <b>the</b> blue strip at {{the bottom}} and red lettering with the two 'X's interlinked together, was designed by noted industrial stylist Raymond Loewy. The interlinked 'X's are incorporated in the modern-day ExxonMobil corporate logo, but <b>the</b> original <b>Exxon</b> logo continues for marketing and station signage. MAD Magazine spoofed the logo by showing a huge sign above the White House: [...] "NIXXON" [...] with the caption: [...] "..but it's still the same old gas!" ...|$|R
