25|$|In April 2012, a {{crude oil}} pipeline, from <b>the</b> <b>Exxon</b> Corp Baton Rouge Refinery, burst and spilled at least 1,900 {{barrels of oil}} (80,000 gallons) in the rivers of Point Coupee Parish, Louisiana, {{shutting}} down <b>the</b> <b>Exxon</b> Corp Baton Refinery for a few days. Regulators opened an investigation {{in response to the}} pipeline oil spill.|$|E
